  "text": "Antenatal calcium supplementation is an important component of the comprehensive strategy to address perinatal morbidity due to preeclampsia [CITATION_1] . We examined factors influencing adoption and acceptability of the WHO guidelines on calcium supplementation for prevention of pre-eclampsia in a rural Kenyan population. The TIPs approach provided a rich set of data to inform a complex set of research questions. To our knowledge, this is the first study to assess multiple features of the guidelines, which might influence adoption, acceptability, and adherence among pregnant women, in the household setting.",
